* Iron Raptor looked at Prowl as he came to stand beside her for support, his concerned question still hanging in the air.
She was more tired then wounded and all she wanted to do was collapse and sleep, the strain from keeping her Second Beast Mode active was what was causing it.
With a rather tired look she glanced over at Plintissa but then she turned away from her, being the enemy now she wanted nothing to do with her.
Iron Raptor then looked back at Prowl, the concern in his optics still very visible.*

" I'm alright just...so tired."

* Her last words were a bit weak as she then looked ahead of her but then closed her optics for a few moments to rest them but then reopened them, a sudden spasm in her side causing her to gasp but then contain herself as not to worry Prowl any further.
Her steps were still faltered but they carried her slowly towards a CR chamber, although she needed rest more then a repair.
The more she thought about sleep the more tired she became, her wounds could be easily bandaged so that her wounds would not get worse as she slept.
Iron Raptor then leaned against a wall only a few feet from a CR chamber but she didn't take another step towards it, obviously exhausted from the battle as her breathing became a bit heavy but then slowed as her body relaxed against the wall a bit.*
